<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/8–445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-04">4 August 1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>040931. Am advised Soong and new Foreign Minister<note n="9" xml:id="d672fn9">Wang Shih-chieh.</note> arriving Moscow Monday
                            August 6. I will be back in Moscow by then. I request that I be
                            instructed along the lines of my memorandum to you of July 31.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>